article.headline: Green Bay 54, E. Michigan 49
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Kam Serroni and Keifer Sykes led a balanced scoring effort with 10 points apiece as Green Bay earned a nonconference 54-49 victory over Eastern Michigan on Saturday. Alec Brown and Brennan Cougill each scored nine points for Green Bay (12-14). Both made major contributions to a 41-29 rebounding advantage -- Brown with 13 and Cougill with eight. Brown also had four blocked shots and three assists. Darrell Lampley led Eastern Michigan (11-16) with 13 points, giving his team a 26-14 scoring advantage off the bench. Starting guard Derek Thompson scored 12. Eastern Michigan also scored 15 points off turnovers, Green Bay seven.
